<item>
            <title>[HBASE-12211] hbase-daemon.sh direct the ulimit output to log .out instead of log .log?</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12211</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the hbase-daemon.sh file line 199, it has the content:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo &quot;`ulimit -a`&quot; &amp;gt;&amp;gt; $loglog 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The variable loglog is defined as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;logout=$HBASE_LOG_DIR/$HBASE_LOG_PREFIX.out&lt;br/&gt;
loggc=$HBASE_LOG_DIR/$HBASE_LOG_PREFIX.gc&lt;br/&gt;
loglog=&quot;$&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;Unknown macro: {HBASE_LOG_DIR}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;/$&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;Unknown macro: {HBASE_LOGFILE}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For my understanding, this information should be printed to the &quot;logout&quot; variable; we should not mix this &quot;ulimit&quot; information with the actual log printed by hbase java program.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
